Description: You have visited a house that worships stories.
Name: _REUSE

Description: One day, this will be your nation's flag. [Equip to an Auxiliary slot.]
Name: A Banner of Coming Glory

Description: A boxful of mystery. Open it!
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|You have finished opening a cache of curiosities.
Name: A Cache of Curiosities

Description: It was the Laconic General who named the Carnelian Coast. Then she discovered it was full of sapphires. Imagine her embarrassment.
Name: A Casket of Sapphires

Description: This dreamy, furtive fellow is travelling to the Principles of Coral.
Name: A Chequered Character

Description: There is much still to discover here. But this will suffice for now.
Name: A Comprehensive Port Report: Empire of Hands

Description: A somewhat less than frank and full description of affairs.
AvailableAt: Aigul
Name: A Compromised Port Report: Aigul

Description: An invitation to meet the Delightful Adventuress at the University. (This continues the Empire of Hands story)
Name: A Delightful Invitation

Description: Take it to the Empire of Hands for a reward
Name: A Delivery of Hydrogen

Description: You have professional, perhaps even qualified, medical assistance.
Name: A Doctor Aboard

Description: This is a chapter of the Crimson Book, that notorious compilation of love stories long-sought by the Masters of the Bazaar.
Name: A Dream of Red

Description: Highly profitable, if you have no principles. [This stuff is too dangerous even to be properly illegal. Be cautious in taking it to London.]
Name: A Firkin of Red Honey

Description: Suspended in what feels like a chip of zee-salt. The Exquisite Seneschal of the Empire of Hands claims it will be useful.
Name: A Frozen Drop of Red Honey
A Gift for the Monkey Emperor

Description: Fresh from the Surface, only a little bruised.
Name: A Gift for the Pirate-King

Description: It is beautifully enamelled. Its eyes glisten like digestive fluid.
Name: A Gift for the Wistful Deviless

Description: A sign of the trust of the Pirate-King of the Isle of Cats.
Name: A Key to the Cage-Gardens

Description: He wouldn't be painted without his hat.
Name: A Locket with a Dapper Chap's Portrait

Description: She never quite smiles.
Name: A Locket with a Likely Lass' Portrait

Description: One zailor's treasure is another zailor's junk. But this looks interesting...
Name: A Long-Buried Treasure

Description: It blazes with apocyanic radiance. Wars have been fought for less. [You may find a use for this: or the Alarming Scholar will certainly purchase it.]
Name: A Lump of Blue Scintillack

Description: Not miracles, really. But they'll never get close enough to see the difference.
Name: A Manual of Miracles

Description: Unsealed, but written in one of the more esoteric scripts of Hell.
Name: A Message from the Wistful Deviless

Description: A sullen viric glow leaks from within. Sometimes it rattles. Best not open it.
Name: A Mirrorcatch Box Full of Very Angry Dream-Snakes

Description: Dream-greeh snake-skin and scraps of close-written paper
Name: A Mirror-Charm

Description: The Cladery Heir removed something from you.
AvailableAt: The Cladery Heir can do this surgery.
Name: A Missing Earlobe

Description: You've welcomed a stranger aboard your ship. This may lead to complications.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Consequences wait.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Welcome aboard, stranger.~0|A certain matter has become clear.
Name: A New Face

Description: "A wakes APOCYAN, the blue of memory and brightest coral."
Name: A Page from 'The Neathbow': Apocyan

Description: "C lights COSMOGONE, the colour of remembered suns. The fecund, the foetid, the fungal: these flourish in the glow of cosmogone."
Name: A Page from 'The Neathbow': Cosmogone

Description: "G is lost in GANT, which remains when all other colours are eaten. Gant can be found where shadows are myriad."
Name: A Page from 'The Neathbow': Gant

Description: "I is for IRRIGO. No one remembers why. Irrigo colours the forgotten corners of home."
Name: A Page from 'The Neathbow': Irrigo

Description: "P drowns in PELIGIN, the colour of the deepest zee. [Someone has scrawled in the margin: BEYOND THE GATE THERE IS A SEA MORE SUNLESS]"
Name: A Page from 'The Neathbow': Peligin

Description: "V marks VIOLANT when blood is shed in a spired place. Violant ink is employed for the most desperate treaties..."
Name: A Page from 'The Neathbow': Violant

Description: "Behind your mirror, V names VIRIC, the colour of shallow sleep."
Name: A Page from 'The Neathbow': Viric

Description: Something inexplicable from Irem. Will it really protect against sunlight?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Before now, you didn't have the Parabox.~0|Before now, you had the Parabox.
Name: A Parabox

Description: Provided by the Exquisite Seneschal to kill the Cannibal Pirates plaguing the Empire of Hands.
Name: A Particularly Potent Poison

Description: The way to the Surface, and a marvel of engineering. The Admiralty has a very modest interest.
Name: A Perfunctory Port Report: the Cumaean Canal

Description:
A study of a clearing amid trees that do not grow in the Neath, of a zee-captain smashing the image of a painted serpent. The zee-captain's crew look on calmly. A forked tongue is visible in one's open mouth. The painting is tinted everywhere with viric - the greenish colour of shallow sleep, which cannot be seen on the surface of the world.
You are the zee-captain in the painting; you are also the painter.
Name: A Phantasmal Encounter, 189-, Captain ------

Description: The nuns endure.
Name: A Port Report: Abbey Rock

Description: Gateway to the Elder Continent! Devourer of the naive.
Name: A Port Report: Adam's Way

Description: The light dazzles and burns. Few can tolerate its strength.
Name: A Port Report: Aestival

Description: A report of doings in the Fortas Kettle at Aigul.
AvailableAt: Aigul
Name: A Port Report: Aigul

Description: A report of the doings in the flourishing port.
AvailableAt: Acquire at Anthe
Name: A Port Report: Anthe

Description: You have seen where the world ends. Behind those peaks of ice, something colder by far.
Name: A Port Report: Avid Horizon

Description: The exiles do not speak, and the monkeys merely chatter grumpily. Still, there is information to be gleaned here.
Name: A Port Report: Codex

Description: A description of how things stand at Dahut.
AvailableAt: This must be assembled at Dahut.
Name: A Port Report: Dahut

Description: Recent events out on the edge of London's interests.
Name: A Port Report: Demeaux Island

Description: The latest news from the island of soul-stealing apes. Technically, monkeys.
Name: A Port Report: Empire of Hands

Description: Yezz. Yezz. We know zzo much. We are home.
Name: A Port Report: Fallen London

Description: Pristine towers of zee ice. An encampment of questions and riddles.
Name: A Port Report: Frostfound

Description: The Admiralty, among others, is always interested in pirate business.
Name: A Port Report: Gaider's Mourn

Description: A fallen stalactite: a monastery filled with plunder.
Name: A Port Report: Godfall

Description: Efficient workers sing vigorously. Keen eyes observe.
Name: A Port Report: Grand Geode

Description: A city in constant repair, set upon the back of a great beast. The price of peace is profound.
Name: A Port Report: Hideaway

Description: An odd place. Best to keep an eye on it.
Name: A Port Report: Hunter's Keep

Description: You will have been there.
Name: A Port Report: Irem

Description: A dissolute smugglers' haven of alehouses and honey-dens.
Name: A Port Report: Isle of Cats

Description: The lights are gone from the Keep.
Name: A Port Report: Keep's End

Description: Bright, dark, fierce, soft, rich, desperate. A complicated place: like London.
Name: A Port Report: Khan's Heart

Description: Long-moored ships provide shelter for exiles.
Name: A Port Report: Khan's Shadow

Description: This is the place the world ends.
Name: A Port Report: Kingeater's Castle

Description: Some truth may be gleaned amidst exaggeration and falsehood.
AvailableAt: This must be assembled at Low Barnet.
Name: A Port Report: Low Barnet

Description: A detailed report on a place of interest. The Admiralty would value it.
Name: A Port Report: Mt Palmerston

Description: A great mouth in the zee-floor, home to a lawless, aquatic culture.
Name: A Port Report: Nook

Description: The statue's hard to miss.
Name: A Port Report: Nuncio

Description: Two houses, both alike in dignity. Which isn't saying much.
Name: A Port Report: Pigmote Isle

Description: THE CITY CRIES OUT.
Name: A Port Report: Polythreme

Description: How fares Little London?
Name: A Port Report: Port Carnelian

Description: The curious business of the Principles perplexes and intrigues London.
Name: A Port Report: Port Cecil

Description: You never find much news on Mutton Island, but it's intelligence for the Admiralty nevertheless.
Name: A Port Report: Quaker's Haven

Description: Factory, Emporium, and Home of the Underwater Cigar.
Name: A Port Report: Rosegate

Description: Intriguing. How could so many people have missed so many sorrow-spiders?
Name: A Port Report: Saviour's Rocks

Description: It was a nice place once. Well, no it wasn't.
Name: A Port Report: Saviour's Rocks (Destroyed)

Description: The City of Memory, where history is a battleground.
Name: A Port Report: Scrimshander

Description: Something has happened, or so somebody claimed.
Name: A Port Report: Shepherd Isles

Description: On the very edge of London's influence, curious matters are conducted.
Name: A Port Report: Station III

Description: A million candles glow. A congregation gathers.
Name: A Port Report: The Chapel of Lights

Description: The remains of a vast turtle shell. Voracious hunters. Rotting flesh.
Name: A Port Report: The Chelonate

Description: Only a tiny portion of the Hold is visible. But you can learn much from the comings and goings of those who visit.
Name: A Port Report: The Fathomking's Hold

Description: The forgotten depths where the elder beasts of the zee go to die.
Name: A Port Report: The Gant Pole

Description: "A concept is a brick. It can be used to build a courthouse of reason. Or it can be thrown through the window."
Name: A Port Report: The Iron Republic

Description: The philosophers of the swamp debate, squabble and pray.
Name: A Port Report: The Mangrove College

Description: Blow by blow, the scholars convert stone to secrets.
Name: A Port Report: The Salt Lions

Description: There's only one of it. For now.
Name: A Port Report: The Uttershroom

Description: Far below a lonely lighthouse...
Name: A Port Report: Undercrow

Description: The brightly lit town of Varchas allows visitors in limited numbers.
Name: A Port Report: Varchas

Description: Once bright, Varchas is now dark. The silence is malevolent.
Name: A Port Report: Varchas, Broken

Description: Varchas is brightly lit. The doors are locked. Outsiders are not permitted.
Name: A Port Report: Varchas, Closed to Outsiders

Description: Tomb-colonists fill their idle hours with conspiracy. Some of the conspiracies are of interest in London.
Name: A Port Report: Venderbight

Description: What were they today? What were you?
Name: A Port Report: Visage

Description: Why are there so many questions in Whither?
Name: A Port Report: Whither

Description: A prison island. Or the knot-oracles' larder.
Name: A Port Report: Wisdom

Description: Where the wreckers write poetry. Where love is known.
Name: A Port Report: Wrack

Description: Violant: the colour of necessary, but troublesome connections. According to other traditions, the colour of blood shed in a spired place. It's very hard to forget anything you've written in violant ink...
Name: A Pot of Violant Ink

Description: You travelled through a white wood, and returned with a notion.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|A cane of pale wood~2|A silvery restorative
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have what you came for.~0|You have discharged your duty to the Cheery Man.
Name: A Remedy for the Cheery Man

Description: Someone in London requires your services.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Someone is looking for passage~5|You welcomed a passenger aboard
ChangeDescriptionText: 5|Welcome!~1|Someone is looking for passage.
Name: A Request for Passage

Description: "There's this little place in Venderbight..."
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|You've found the Vengeance of Jonah~1|You've been told of an exceptionally fine restaurant in Venderbight.
Name: A Restaurant Recommendation

Description: Found on the Empire of Hands' beach of corpses.
AvailableAt: The picture of a small blonde baby is inside.
Name: A Rusty Locket

Description: This Clay Man looks confused as it grasps the Mirrorcatch Box in its great grey hands. It would look a lot more confused if it knew what to expect. [This will allow the Tireless Mechanic to get a night's sleep.]
Name: A Serpent-Trap

Description: This taciturn woman has business in the Corsair's Forest.
Name: A Shady Sort

Description: A melody from Wrack
AvailableAt: One may record the song in Wrack.
Name: A Song of Broken Hulls

Description: A past yet to be revealed
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|Your "A Stranger" quality has gone. Welcome to the world!~1|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 1. This will unlock more stories.~2|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 2. This will unlock more stories.~3|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 3. This will unlock more stories.~4|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 4. This will unlock more stories.~5|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 5. This will unlock more stories.~6|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 6. This will unlock more stories.~7|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 7. This will unlock more stories.~8|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 8. This will unlock more stories.~9|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 9. This will unlock more stories.~10|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 10. This will unlock more stories.~11|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 11. This will unlock more stories.~12|You started with a quality called "A Stranger", which has just changed to level 12. This will unlock more stories.~1000|Welcome.
Name: a stranger

Description: This is the story of the star. An exile from the High Wilderness took up a mask and a burden, and recorded its pilgrimage here below. There is no happy ending.
Name: A Travelling Light

LevelDescriptionText: 1|London~2|Khanate~3|Corsair~4|Zubmarine
Name: A Wreck

Description: To convert your ship for zubmarine travel, visit the old sapphire processing plant in Port Carnelian.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your future captains may convert their ships to zubmarines without cost.
Name: A Zubmarine Zecret

Description: There is something in the deeper depths.
LevelDescriptionText: 4|Abyss of Graves~2|Abyss of Pyres~3|Abyss of Pomegranates~1|Abyss of Scriptures
Name: Abyssal Rites: Above an Abyss

Description: She waits in the dark.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You performed the Ritual of Greeting~2|You performed the Ritual of Hearths~3|You performed the Ritual of Feasting~5|You are face to face with Her Ladyship~4|She is here~10|Lady Black will remember you
ChangeDescriptionText: 5|You are face to face with Her Ladyship.~4|She is here.~10|Lady Black will remember you.~1|You have made yourself known.~2|You have purified yourself.~3|You have satisfied yourself.
Name: Abyssal Rites: Approaching Her Ladyship

Description: What are you hoping to find in these depths?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Good luck.~0|You rise from the abyss.
Name: Abyssal Rites: Diving...

Description: You are not as you were before.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|You have forsaken a rite~1|The Rite of Greeting [This has increased your Hearts by 20 and reduced your Iron by 10.]~2|The Rite of Hearths [This has increased your Mirrors by 20 and reduced your Veils by 10.]~3|The Rite of Feasting [This has increased your Iron by 20 and reduced your Mirrors by 10.]~4|The Rite of Solace [This has increased your Veils by 20 and reduced your Hearts by 10.]
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have partaken in the Rite of Greeting.~2|You have partaken in the Rite of Hearths.~3|You have partaken in the Rite of Feasting.~34|You have partaken in the Rite of Solace.
Name: Abyssal Rites: Rite

Description: What happened to the youngest sister?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Lost in a Fire~2|New Sisters~3|Dark Duties~10|Above the Gulf of Corinth
Name: Acquaintance: Phoebe's Fate

Description: You've been known to visit the three sisters of Hunter's Keep.
LevelDescriptionText: 2|You are acquainted with the sisters~1|You know something of Hunter's Keep~20|You are acquainted with the sisters, but something has changed.
ChangeDescriptionText: 2|You are acquainted with the sisters of Hunter's Keep.~10|You are acquainted with the sisters, but something has changed.~1|You know something of Hunter's Keep~25|You've explored the silent house on Hunter's Keep~31|The house on Hunter's Keep is aflame!~40|The house on Hunter's Keep is a blackened shell
Name: Acquaintance: Sojourning with the Sisters

Description: The deep cannot hide its secrets from you.
LevelDescriptionText: 10|The Fierce Philanthropist will help you convert your ship to a zubmarine at her hidden workshop~20|Retrieve zonar schematics from Station III or Khan's Shadow~30|Return the zonar schematics to the hidden workshop in Port Carnelian
ChangeDescriptionText: 10|The Fierce Philanthropist will help you convert your ship to a zubmarine at her hidden workshop.~20|Retrieve zonar schematics from Station III or Khan's Shadow.~30|Return the zonar schematics to the hidden workshop in Port Carnelian.~0|The zubmarine conversion process is complete!
Name: Acquiring a Zubmarine

Description: You were guest of honour at one of the funeral-feasts of the Replete.
Name: Adam's Way: a Guest at a Red Table

Description: It is planted in the morning, grows tall by lunch, buds in the afternoon, and withers in the evening. Foreigners must return to their ships before it falls.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Tree of a Single Day is a hopeful sapling, green and budding.~2|The Tree of a Single Day is tall and strong. Its branches stretch over the rooftops.~3|The Tree of a Single Day is flowering. White petals drift across the square.~5|The Tree of a Single Day cracks and leans. It is time to return to your ship.~4|The Tree of a Single Day is withered. Its gnarled trunk groans.
Name: Adam's Way: the Tree of a Single Day

Description: How do they speak to you?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Madam~2|Sir~3|Citizen~4|my lord~5|my lady~6|Captain~100|(mumble)
Name: Addressed as

Description: [This provides the advice snippet storylet. Sell it to remove this advice storylet.]
Name: ADVICE FOR CAPTAINS

Description: How well do you know the First Mate of the Fortas Kettle?
AvailableAt: Gain acquaintance at Aigul.
LevelDescriptionText: 20|Seen them through at least one mission~30|Learned some of their deeper secrets~40|Old acquaintances~50|Asked an important question~60|Persuaded the First Mate to abandon Aigul~5|Gained hospitality through a gift of Solacefruits~10|Observed the formation of spines
Name: Aigul: Acquaintance with the First Mate

Description: The Imperious Sister has asked you to investigate the regrets of her Brother.
AvailableAt: Gain at Mount Palmerston or Scrimshander, continue at Aigul.
LevelDescriptionText: 10|Received a commission~20|Begun drilling for a regret~30|Halfway through drilling for a regret~60|Delivered a regret by way of the Mirror Marches~70|Delivered a regret by way of Prisoner's Honey~80|Delivered a regret in spine form~40|Abandoned drilling for a regret  you may tell the Sister so at Hunter's Keep~45|Advised the sister about abandonment at Hunter's Keep~5|Stopped to listen to the Imperious Sister~55|Grew a regret into spine form~90|Learned the outcome of sending a dream~50|Retrieved a regret. What form will you deliver it in?
Name: Aigul: Commissioned to Retrieve a Regret

Description: The First Mate grows Needles of Fortas while exploring Aigul, but how many?
AvailableAt: Aigul
Name: Aigul: First Mate's Sensitivity

Description: The question one must ask the First Mate of the Fortas Kettle.
AvailableAt: Aigul
Name: Aigul: Knowledge of the First Mate's Question

Description: Expressions of the First Mate's grief at exploring the bitterness of Aigul.
AvailableAt: Aigul
Name: Aigul: Needle of Fortas

Description: This content is structured but not yet written - AK to complete.
Name: AKContent

Description: AK to add quality reqs and other mechanics.
Name: AKMechanics

Description: A carpenter, weaver, engineer's hand and rat of all work.
Name: Albino Tinkerer

Description: A thinking creature made this, or the sea made this; or both.
Name: Ambiguous Eolith

Description: He claims he has no interest in the Seven Against Nidah. [Reduce this to 0 to change his mind.]
ChangeDescriptionText: 2|When you finish your tale, Batuk asks a question. He contemplates your answer.~1|Batuk attends closely as you speak.~0|After your tale, Batuk springs to his feet and paces the cavity.~4|Batuk claims he will not rejoin the Seven.~3|Batuk feigns indifference, but you you can tell he's listening.
Name: Ambition: Batuk's Indifference

Description: It is said that seven once tried to democratise death.
LevelDescriptionText: 10|Begin your quest in London~20|Seek Isery, on the Isle of Cats~30|Seek the Fierce Philanthropist, at Port Carnelian~35|Search the cities beneath the zee for the Fierce Philanthropist's husband~40|Find the Fierce Philanthropist's husband at Low Barnet, near London~50|Ask Lytton about the Seven Against Nidah~60|Find Mariam, deep in Scrimshander's ivory Archives~200|With Mariam, plan the conquest of Nidah~70|Restore the Seven Against Nidah~300|Seven years pass...~1000|Seven Conquered Nidah~2000|One Conquered Nidah~3000|Nidah stands, and you were rewarded with a kingdom
ChangeDescriptionText: 10|Begin your quest in London.~20|Pursue your ambition on the Isle of Cats.~30|Pursue your ambition at Port Carnelian, with the Fierce Philanthropist.~35|You must search the cities beneath the zee...~40|Find the Philanthropist's husband at Low Barnet, near London.~50|You have given the Philanthropist's locket to Lytton.~60|Pursue your ambition at Scrimshander - seek Mariam in the Ivory Archives.~70|You must restore the Seven Against Nidah.~200|Prepare your plans to conquer Nidah.~300|Seven years pass...~1000|Seven Conquered Nidah.~2000|One Conquered Nidah.~3000|Nidah was saved, and its saviour rewarded.
Name: Ambition: Death Hath no more Dominion

Description: How will you overcome the Presbyter's numberless legions?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Find a way to defeat the Presbyter's armies.~0|You have begun a scheme to defeat the Presbyter's armies.
Name: Ambition: Nidah's Armies

Description: Search the cities of the deep for the Fierce Philanthropist's missing husband.
ChangeDescriptionText: 10|You are searching for Lytton.
Name: Ambition: Searching for Lytton

Description: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Aigul?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Lytton in Aigul, the City of Regrets.
Name: Ambition: Seeking Lytton: Aigul

Description: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Anthe?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Lytton in Anthe, the City of Flowers.
Name: Ambition: Seeking Lytton: Anthe

Description: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Dahut?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Lytton in Dahut, the City of Peace.
Name: Ambition: Seeking Lytton: Dahut

Description: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Hideaway?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Lytton in Hideaway, the City of Refuge.
Name: Ambition: Seeking Lytton: Hideaway

Description: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Nook?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Lytton in Nook, the City of Freedom.
Name: Ambition: Seeking Lytton: Nook

Description: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Scrimshander?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Lytton in Scrimshander, the City of Rememberance.
Name: Ambition: Seeking Lytton: Scrimshander

Description: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Wrack?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Seek Lytton in Wrack, the City of Delights.
Name: Ambition: Seeking Lytton: Wrack

Description: Who will command the Seven's fleets?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have yet to recruit someone~5|Arik
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Seven need a fleet-captain.~5|The Seven have found their fleet-captain.
Name: Ambition: the Captain

Description: Who will fund the reformed Seven against Nidah?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have yet to recruit one~5|The Fierce Philanthropist
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Seven require a financier.~5|The Seven have found their financier.
Name: Ambition: the Financier

Description: Who will lead the way to Nidah?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have yet to recruit someone~5|Isery~3|Seek Isery, on the Isle of Cats
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Seven require a guide.~5|The Seven have found their guide.~3|Isery, who dwells on the Isle of Cats, may replace Lorenzo.
Name: Ambition: the Guide

Description: Who will protect the Seven against the Presbyterate's numberless dangers?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have yet to recruit someone~10|The Banded Prince~5|Rosina~3|If Rosina cannot help, perhaps the Banded Prince of the Carnelian Coast can replace her
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Seven require a healer.~5|The Seven have found their healer.
Name: Ambition: the Healer

Description: Who will spread the word?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have yet to recruit someone~5|Bourdain, or what is left of him~3|If you cannot retrieve Bourdain, a Voracious London Diplomat may make a suitable replacement~10|The Voracious Diplomat
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Seven require a Propagandist.~5|The Seven have found their Propogandist.~3|Perhaps a Voracious London Diplomat could replace Bourdain.
Name: Ambition: the Propagandist

Description: Nidah lies deep in the interior of the Elder Continent, beyond jungle, desert and plain. How will you reach it?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Find a way to reach Nidah.~0|You have begun a scheme to reach Nidah.
Name: Ambition: the Road to Nidah

Description: You must restore the Seven Against Nidah.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|One of Seven~2|Two of Seven~3|Three of Seven~4|Four of Seven~5|Five of Seven~6|Six of Seven~7|Seven of Seven
ChangeDescriptionText: 7|The Seven Against Nidah are reformed.~1|You have recruited someone to the Seven.
Name: Ambition: the Seven, Anew

Description: Who will command the Seven's legions?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have yet to recruit someone~5|Batuk~3|Convince Batuk to rejoin the Seven
ChangeDescriptionText: 5|The Seven have found their commander.~1|The Seven need a commander.~3|Perhaps you can convince Batuk to rejoin the Seven.
Name: Ambition: the Soldier

Description: They are taller than the Empress' Palace, thicker than the length of a dreadnought, and built from black basalt. How are you to breach them?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Find a way to breach Nidah's walls.~0|You have begun a scheme to breach Nidah's walls.
Name: Ambition: the Walls of Nidah

Description: It is, fortunately, sleeping.
Name: An Additional Eye on an Unobtrusive Part of your Person

Description: The account a certain zubmarine crew's dreams, after their captain was allegedly taken by Lady Black.
Name: An Adumbration of Her Heart

Description: Now you look more closely, it appears to be new parchment stained with what smells like... coffee?
Name: An Ancient-Ish Treasure Map

Description: A notarised copy rests securely in the vaults of Baseborn & Fowlingpiece. Another, in the vaults of the Bazaar itself. [This will ensure your next character inherits your Lodgings, along with any Heirlooms you have stored there.]
Name: An Ironclad Will

Description: They won't cure the Brisk Campaigner, but perhaps they'll grant her a little more time.
Name: An Unlikely Collection of Treatments

Description: An appalling glob of organic matter and dripping fluids, retrieved from somewhere you'd rather not think about.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have an Unprepossessing Mass
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have an Unprepossessing Mass.
Name: An Unprepossessing Mass

Description: Death, laid out for your careful inspection.
Name: Anatomical Cabinet

Description: Precious time away from a captain's duties. How will you spend it? [You get one of these each time you return to London.]
Name: Another Day: A Free Evening

Description: Notepaper from Benthic College. He'd like to speak to you.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Alarming Scholar has invited you to call on her (him?)
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|Your business with the Alarming Scholar is concluded, for now.~1|The Alarming Scholar has invited you to call on her (him?) at the University
Name: Another Day: A Message from the Alarming Scholar

Description: Someone wants to sign on!
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Someone wants to sign on!
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Someone wants to sign on!~0|You have no more recruits for the moment.
Name: Another Day: A New Recruit?

Description: The Blind Bruiser attends to business on the dock.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Blind Bruiser attends to business on the dock
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Blind Bruiser attends to business on the dock.~0|The Blind Bruiser has departed.
Name: Another Day: A Visit from a Blind Bruiser

LevelDescriptionText: 1|The remains of countless stories surround you
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Skulls whisper~11|Bones rattle~31|Shadows flicker~41|Stories end~51|Hearts falter~61|Empires crumble~21|Flesh fails~71|Light dims~81|Love dies~91|Dreams lie~100|Memories deceive
Name: Another Day: Dead Bones and Dread Tales

Description: Out with the old laws, in with the new.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Parliament of Flies is open for business~5|The Calvary Doctrine is open for business~10|The Gesundheit Conspiracy is open for business~15|The Expulsus is open for business
Name: Another Day: Iron Republic Days

LevelDescriptionText: 1|Something's out there
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Horrors walk~11|Darkness coils~21|Dreams wait~31|Stone drops~41|Echo, echo...~51|Light flares~61|Wind gusts~91|Hearts pound~92|A child screams~81|Silence...silence~94|Pits gape~71|Shadows flicker~95|Still water~96|Distant laughter~97|Scuffed footsteps~98|Pale fungus~93|Spiders scuttle~99|Memories...~100|(Don't look)
Name: Another Day: Nasty Things in the Dark

Description: Travel deep enough, and you'll find something interesting.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|You've returned from the swamps!
ChangeDescriptionText: 10|Shrieks and chitters...~20|Eyes in the undernight...~30|Spreading ripples...~40|Swags of hanging fungus...~50|Fat white mosquitoes...~60|Shrieking cockatoos...~70|Sulphurous stirrings...~80|A dribble of sticky rain...~90|A moss-furred boat-skeleton...~1|Black and stinking mud...~100|A soft phosphorescence...
Name: Another Day: Navigating the Swamps

Description: Perhaps a payment awaits you.
Name: Another Day: Pirate's Pleasure

Description: A market for collectors and eccentrics throngs on Roser's Wharf.
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|The Rose-Market has concluded, for now.~1|The Rose-Market bustles on Roser's Wharf. Who will be there today?
Name: Another Day: The Rose-Market

Description: Your time at zee will change you... and London.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Ever-changing
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Something has changed in the Neath
Name: Another Day: Time, the Healer

Description: The prizes you've taken await you in London. Claim them at your Lodgings.
Name: Another Day: To the Victor, the Spoils

Description: What's down here?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are at the edge of the Citadel.~2|You are in the second tangle of tunnels.~3|You are in the third tangle of tunnels.~5|You are in the fifth tangle of tunnels.~6|You are in the sixth tangle of tunnels.~7|You are in the seventh tangle of tunnels.~8|You have reached the Citadel's root...~9|You have entered the Citadel's root...~4|You have reached the mid-point of the Citadel
Name: Another Day: Venturing into the Shattered Citadel

Description: Someone would like to call on you at your Lodgings.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Someone would like to call on you at your Lodgings.
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|Visitors have departed.~1|Someone would like to call on you at your Lodgings.
Name: Another Day: Visitors

Description: You are learning the Waswood's silent paths. [Increase this to 7 to find what you seek.]
Name: Another Day: Where the Wood Was

Description: Is your tongue a supple diamond? Does your speech glitter and stab?
AvailableAt: Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Hard-tongued
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your tongue is transparent and its edges are perfectly squared.
Name: Anthe: Acumination of the Tongue

Description: Have you used your sharpness to enhance a particular skill?
AvailableAt: Only long work at Anthe will gain you an Anthean advantage.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Mirrors~2|Pages~3|Hearts~4|Iron
Name: Anthe: Anthean Advantage

Description: A work of romantic literature that has been revised by the best Anthean minds.
Name: Anthe: Anthean Romance

Description: Are your lungs a geode, hollow and sparkling?
AvailableAt: Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Barb-lunged
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your respiration slows. Your exhalations are cold and dry.
Name: Anthe: Barbing of the Lungs

Description: How much sharpness can you endure?
AvailableAt: Cultivate this at Anthe.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You can go sharp, but only in one area.~2|You can be sharp in two ways.~3|Triple sharpness will not harm you. You can endure it.~4|Quadruple sharpness? Yes. Why not? Half of you is sharp, but will you mind?~5|You are capable of being more than half crystal.~6|Six. Six sharpnesses.~7|Total
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You can now take on a single sharpness.~2|You can now take on another sharpness.~7|You can hold seven sharpnesses. Seven is the maximum.
Name: Anthe: Capacity for Sharpness

Description: Are you transparent? Do you display your ligatures to the world?
AvailableAt: Found at Anthe.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Transparent
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You crackle when you move.
Name: Anthe: Clarity of the Skin

Description: Rosina's Onlookers are now infected with animescence, and haunt the place.
AvailableAt: Acquired at Anthe.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Conflagranti wander the chambers of Anthe, suffering from and trying to spread their animescence.~2|Anthe has been cleansed of Conflagranti.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Anthe is now haunted by Conflagranti.~2|Anthe is now free of Conflagranti.
Name: Anthe: Conflagranti

Description: Your liver is impervious to any abuse.
AvailableAt: Gain in the first chamber of Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Crystal-livered
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your liver has turned to a crystalline sieve.
Name: Anthe: Crystallization of Liver

Description: A report for Khan's Glory
AvailableAt: Begin at Khan's Glory and continue at Anthe.
LevelDescriptionText: 10|You are retrieving information from Anthe for Khan's Glory.~15|You are searching Anthe's sharp-tongued chambers for information to return to Khan's Glory.~20|You are returning information to Khan's Glory from Anthe.~30|You have reliably informed Khan's Glory about a matter in Anthe.
ChangeDescriptionText: 10|You are retrieving information from Anthe for Khan's Glory.~20|You are searching Anthe's sharp-tongued chambers for information to return to Khan's Glory.~30|You are returning information to Khan's Glory from Anthe.~40|You have reliably informed Khan's Glory about a matter in Anthe.
Name: Anthe: Flourishing Intelligence

Description: Any part of the body can go sharp.
AvailableAt: Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Bristle-groined
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your dimensions do not change, only your substance.
Name: Anthe: Flourishing of the Groin

Description: How many places have you gone sharp?
AvailableAt: Anthe provides the opportunity of sharpness.
Name: Anthe: Number of Sharpnesses

AvailableAt: Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 10|Carrying an exile back to Polythreme~20|Delivered an exile back to Polythreme~5|Encountered a Polythreme Exile who was sharp in lung and bone
Name: Anthe: Polythreme Exile

Description: You have looked around Anthe's outermost chambers.
AvailableAt: Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You've seen the outer chambers of Anthe and learned what the place is.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You've seen the outer chambers of Anthe and learned what the place is.
Name: Anthe: Preliminary Visit

Description: How well do you know Rosina?
AvailableAt: Interact with Rosina at Anthe.
Name: Anthe: Rosina's Acquaintance

Description: Did she survive her animescence?
LevelDescriptionText: 10|Recovered~20|Deceased
Name: Anthe: Rosina's Fate

Description: How close is Rosina to death by animescence?
AvailableAt: Rosina's health alters depending on events at Anthe.
LevelDescriptionText: 0|Extremely ill~3|Heating quickly~6|Feverish~9|A bit warm~10|Almost stable~17|Nearly recovered~11|Showing signs of improvement~14|Almost cool
Name: Anthe: Rosina's Health

Description: Gained in the first chamber of Anthe.
AvailableAt: Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Sharp-spleened
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your spleen is a hexagonal crystal.
Name: Anthe: Sharpness of Spleen

Description: Is your skeleton as keen as it could be?
AvailableAt: Anthe
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Spiny
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your skeleton has sharpened and clarified.
Name: Anthe: Spinosity of Bone

Description: Carved from coral, in the Pulse of the Principles it lay.
Name: Apocyan Chess-Piece

Description: The Revenue Men have removed the most challenging elements, and applied a customs stamp to the title leaf.
Name: Approved Romantic Literature

Description: The last secret?
Name: At Last: Salt's Song

Description: You approach an exaltation.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You spoke your burning name, at last~2|You sacrificed your mortal past~4|In the Pillared City, Salt's Song waits~3|You've unravelled all your fates~5|You gave the Exile to disgrace~6|The Exile earned a kind of grace~7|The Exile turned aside her face~8|Do you recall how we came to that place?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You spoke your burning name, at last~2|You sacrificed your mortal past~3|You've unravelled all your fates~4|In the Pillared City, Salt's Song waits~5|You gave the Exile to disgrace~6|The Exile earned a kind of grace~7|The Exile turned aside her face~8|Do you recall how we came to that place?
Name: At Last: the Threshold

Description: A sky-scarred hunk of meteoric iron, the size of a wheel-barrow. Burning glyphs mark its flanks. A star-spore lives in it. It's watching you. Are you sure you know what you're doing with this thing?
Name: Awakened Seal of the Red Science

Description: Who plucks the flax from the banks of rivers that flow through sleep?
Name: Bale of Parabola-Linen

Description: His mastery of fish-flesh would make an emperor weep.
Name: Bandaged Chef-Paramount

Description: He has an ambition for fish. A great ambition.
AvailableAt: He may sometimes be found in the Tomb-Colonies
Name: Bandaged Poissonnier

Description: You are seen.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You are seen
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are seen.
Name: Beheld

Description: The waves are above you.
Name: Below

Description:
"Like a lane of beams athwart the sea,
Thro' all the circle of the golden year!" [An effective device for seeking enemies.]
Name: Blazing Glim-Lamp

Description: What a keen little mushroom!
Name: Blemmigan Gallivanter

Description: Soft as silence.
Name: Bolts of Spider-Silk

Description: Intelligence gleaned from the Brimstone Convention, the government-in-exile of Hell.
Name: Brimstone Buzzings

Description: She's marched with armies and cured generals. Don't annoy her.
AvailableAt: Sometimes available for hire in London.
Name: Brisk Campaigner

Description: You've been pacing yourself. Let's see them keep up with this!
Name: Burst of Speed!

Description: A ponderous, capacious vessel.
Name: Caligo-class Merchant Cruiser

Description: Devours engine emissions, ensuring that your engine never explodes at Full Power. Also slightly improves your chances of evading enemy attention.
Name: Caminus Yards Avid Suppressor

Description: "IT'S A MONSTER. ARE YOU?" A powerful weapon that relies on Torpedo attacks.
Name: Caminus Yards 'Bandersnatch'

Description: A roaring beast of an engine.
Name: Caminus Yards 'Compulsion'

Description: Speak not of it.
Name: Caminus Yards 'D__nation'

Description: "Caminus Yards: We Have Always Loved You." A powerful weapon that permits Flensing attacks.
Name: Caminus Yards Heart-Ender

Description: "Caminus Yards: Stand Well Back." A weapon of savage and alarming power.
Name: Caminus Yards Hellthrasher

Description: Get Rats Where Rats Are Required, Pneumatically. [In combat, this can deploy Rattus Faber assistants for quicker repairs.]
Name: Caminus Yards Pneumatic Ratsender

Description: This is a marker quality that indicates you have a Cannon weapon equipped.
Name: Cannons

Description: You'll look away, eventually. [If you've made an Ironclad Will, you can convert these into Heirlooms for your successor.]
Name: Captivating Treasure

Description: Sealed and triple-sealed with wax.
Name: Carboy of Primordial Shrieks

Description: This bone bears an account of the Chelonate's great turtle and its death. It challenges established history. It should be delivered to Scrimshander.
Name: Cargo of Answers

Description: How secure is your hold?
Name: Cargo Security

Description: Soft-spoken and a little mystical. How much does she see?
AvailableAt: Sometimes available for hire in London.
Name: Carnelian Exile

Description: The finest output of the Greyfields shroom-yards.
Name: Cask of Mushroom Wine

Description: Increase this to 50 before Mouse reaches 1...
Name: Cat: Getting Warmer

Description: An expert in amputations.
Name: Cladery Heir

Description: A souvenir of one of the Cladery Heir's amputations.
AvailableAt: To be found in various places where the Cladery Heir may perform surgeries.
Name: Cladery Souvenir

Description: Has the Cladery Heir performed a treatment at the Cumaean Locks?
AvailableAt: This can be found at the Cumaean Canal Staging Area.
Name: Cladery Treatment: Cumaean Locks

Description: Has the Cladery Heir performed a treatment at Irem?
AvailableAt: The treatment will occur at Irem.
Name: Cladery Treatment: Irem

Description: You allowed the Cladery Heir to make a postman no longer a postman.
Name: Cladery Treatment: Nuncio

Description: Has the Cladery Heir performed a treatment?
AvailableAt: Port Carnelian
Name: Cladery Treatment: Port Carnelian

Description: GOOD DAY. I WILL NOT CAUSE TROUBLE.
Name: Clay Man, Marked for London

Description: Notable stories seem to turn up where the August Travel-Writer goes.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Bound for Gaider's Mourn~5|A second request~10|Bound for the Cumaean Canal~15|A final request~20|Bound for Khan's Heart~25|The August Travel-Writer enforced an Agreement	~50|The August Travel-Writer - one Robert F. Harris - nearly blew up your ship and zubmarine	~75|The August Travel-Writer - one Robert F. Harris - failed to blow up your ship and zubmarine	~100|You refused to carry the August Travel-Writer any farther
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Bound for Gaider's Mourn.~5|A second request.~10|Bound for the Cumaean Canal.~15|A final request.~20|Bound for Khan's Heart.~25|An Agreement enforced.~100|You refused to carry him any farther.~50|The August Travel-Writer - one Robert F. Harris - nearly blew up your ship and zubmarine.	~75|The August Travel-Writer - one Robert F. Harris - failed in his bomb plot against you.
Name: Closing Chapters

Description: Sentiments and histories coil, prisoned by irrigo as the irrigo is prisoned by amber. Mourn the mind that has passed.
Name: Colossal Fluke-Core

Description: Mostly, it's immobile. Occasionally, it's feral.
Name: Comatose Ferret

Description: Provides some small degree of protection against excisemen searching your ship for contraband.
Name: Concealed Compartment

Description: How secure is your contraband against excisemen?
Name: Contraband Concealment

Description: Strictly speaking, this shouldn't be sold to civilian vessels at all, but the Admiralty has grown more casual of late.
Name: Cotterell & Hathersage 'Admiralty Special'

Description: "DON'T DO IT AGAIN." One of C&H's newer models.
Name: Cotterell & Hathersage 'Denunciation'

Description: A severe disincentive to pursuit.
Name: Cotterell & Hathersage 'Discouragement'

Description: It makes the most tremendous bang. Not what you'd call an elegant weapon, but it does make the most tremendous bang. [The Majesty is the only front-mounted pure cannon: others are torpedoes or flensing weapons.]
Name: Cotterell & Hathersage 'Majesty'

Description: Models No. 1 through No. 3 are not discussed in polite company, but this is a powerful and effective device.
Name: Cotterell & Hathersage 'Manticore No.4'

Description: This device operates in so absurd a manner as not to be easily credited. It does, nevertheless, permit torpedo attacks.
Name: Cotterell & Hathersage Pneumatic Dynamite Torpedo-Gun

Description: "WE SHALL COMPEL ATTENTION." A weapon of respectable power.
Name: Cotterell & Hathersage 'Reproach'

Description: These were poets or murderers or priests... or zee-captains. This crate bears a customs mark.
Name: Crate of Brilliant Human Souls

Description: Clinking, glowing, pleading.
Name: Crate of Human Souls

Description: How many zailors do you have aboard?
Name: Crew

Description: The ability to see through the glamours of the Drownies.
AvailableAt: This ability can be earned at Dahut or in a few other places.
Name: Dahut: Clarity

Description: The depth of your commitment to the beauty of Dahut.
AvailableAt: Increase this at Dahut, through interaction there.
Name: Dahut: Enthralment

Description: How long have you spent in the fields of Dahut?
AvailableAt: Progress this at Dahut, or reset it by leaving and returning when Something Awaits You.
Name: Dahut: Length of stay

Description: You've been asked to find a certain person imprisoned in Dahut.
AvailableAt: Wrack begins this story and Dahut continues it.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Asked to seek and free a prisoner in Dahut~10|Freed a prisoner of Dahut~20|Delivered a prisoner of Dahut to Rosegate~30|Reported back to the Composer at Wrack that the Dahut Prisoner was set free~2|Begun asking about a prisoner in Dahut~15|Brought a Dahut Prisoner to visit her friend in Wrack~3|Saw a prisoner in the Crypt
Name: Dahut: Seeking a Prisoner of Dahut

Description: SHINE WHERE THOU WILT AN THOU HARM NONE. Can the Dawn Machine truly command sunlight? And would you want it to?
Name: Dawn's Law

Description: Undeliverable envelopes.
Name: Dead Post

Description: [Bring this to the shipyard in Venderbight to swap to an alternative ship.]
Name: Deeds to a Steam Yacht

Description: A piece cut from the Bazaar, legally yours.
Name: Deeds to the Cladery Heart

Description: The Neath's greatest explorer, in her own mind at least. Take her and her bodyguard to the Empire of Hands.
Name: Delightful Adventuress

Description: These letters used to be dead, but they now have new addresses on them.
Name: Deliverable Post

Description: Now he has a cause.
Name: Determined Doctor

Description: The nature of these yellowish morsels is unclear, except that they are unlikely to be composed of deceased devils. They are kept in sealed cannisters, possibly as ammunition.
Name: Devilbone Dice

Description: He used to believe in things.
Name: Disillusioned Doctor

Description: It has claws; it has a fierce double beak; but just now it seems disinclined to use them.
Name: Docile Blemmigan

Description: You entered a sacred place.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have despoiled a sacred place.
Name: Doom: Frostfound's Core

Description: The keenest minds are often the most fragile.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Rambling
Name: Doom: Scholar's Madness

Description: You attempted to rescue a prisoner from the prison in the Sea of Lilies...
Name: Doom: Wisdom Forewarned

Description:
'The Monster-Hunter winnows the lesser terrors from the true. She has slain That Which Makes Light in the Deeps, eaten its flesh in remembrance of certain Feasts of the Zee, and fashioned her weapon from its remains. She was human, once.' 
But this Monster-Hunter is ready for a glorious ending. Icarus in Black awaits.
Name: Doomed Monster-Hunter

Description: The awful daring of a moment's supposition which an age of ignorance can never deny. [If you sell this, you may not find it easy to replace.]
Name: Dread Surmise

Description: The Unsettled Salvager is willing to zail far to find her.
LevelDescriptionText: 5|Bound for Polythreme~1|Bound for Venderbight~50|You committed the Unsettled Salvager to the Royal Bethlehem~10|The Unsettled Salvager wants to dive to meet Lady Black again. You could let her, or you could try to find help for her~100|The Unsettled Salvager dived and did not return.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Bound for Venderbight.~5|Bound for Polythreme.~50|Committed to the Royal Bethlehem.~10|She knows what she must do.~100|Into the zee
Name: Dreams of a Lady

Description: A song of worship and adoration from the depths.
AvailableAt: Acquired at Dahut under certain circumstances.
Name: Drownie Hymn

Description: A song of undertows and silt.
AvailableAt: Found at Dahut.
Name: Drownie Love-song

Description: A song of isolation and belonging, of greatness and humility.
AvailableAt: Attained at a price in Dahut.
Name: Drownie Song in Counterpoint

Description: Still chilly from the fingers of Drownies...
Name: Drowning-Pearl

Description: Echoes are the currency of the Bazaar; and, thus, the currency of London.
Name: Echo

Description: A battered, rusting mechanism that will ensure your ship goes in more or less the correct direction.
Name: Elderly Steeple-Engine

Description: A majestically crested bird which speaks only in competent elegiac poetry. It is of a melancholy disposition.
Name: Elegiac Cockatoo

Description: And yet it moves. A piece, emission or work of the Dawn Machine.
Name: Element of Dawn

Description: The Empire of Hands has charged you with arranging deliveries of hydrogen from the Iron Republic.
Name: Empire of Hands: An Infernal Trade Agreement

Description: Whatever the Delightful Adventuress is looking for, it must be worth a fortune. If you contribute, you will be owed a share.
Name: Empire of Hands: Delightful Archaeology
Empire of Hands: Explored Ash Isthmus

Description: The Empire of Hands' most sacred island, to whatever degree the monkeys are capable of such respect.
Name: Empire of Hands: Explored Fountainhead Island

Description: The only human settlement in the Empire of Hands
Name: Empire of Hands: Explored Hearthsake Island

Description: The cruel heart of the whimsical Empire of Hands
Name: Empire of Hands: Explored Sovereign Island

Description: Your current level in the Vault.
Name: Empire of Hands: Exploring the Vault of the First Emperor

Description: You have found adventure in the Empire of Hands
Name: Empire of Hands: Monkey Business

Description: It is not given lightly.
LevelDescriptionText: 2|Your ticket on board the Empire of Hands' Zeppelin. Hopefully it was worth it.~1|The Monkey Emperor's price is high, but if you want to steal his prize...
Name: Empire of Hands: Monkey Emperor's Favour

Description: This. Never. Happened.
Name: Empire of Hands: Quest For Dignity

Description: Well. You thought it was good.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Flying Monkey~2|The Other Name
Name: Empire of Hands: Rejected Zeppelin Name

Description: A box of incendiary documents. Simply being aware of some of them is against laws too secret to have been written.
AvailableAt: If you dare to use this, take it to Fallen London
Name: Empire of Hands: The Monkey Emperor's Wrath

Description: The Empire of Hands will need it to get where it's going.
Name: Empire of Hands: The Zeppelin - Fuel

Description: The Empire of Souls needs them to uplift its unblessed civilians.
Name: Empire of Hands: The Zeppelin - Souls

Description: The Empire of Hands will need them all where it's going.
Name: Empire of Hands: The Zeppelin - Supplies

Description: A child could solve this. Eventually...
Name: Empire of Hands: Towers of Hanoi Moves Remaining
Empire of Hands: Treasure Valley X
Empire of Hands: Treasure Valley Y

Description: Your soul resides in the Empire of Hands
Name: Empire of Hands: Unlicensed Spirifage

Description: Your current standing in the Monkey Court.
AvailableAt: Raise it by trading, supplying the Zeppelin, or amusing the fickle Pentecost Apes.
Name: Empire of Hands: Wildweald Status

Description: A chest with an embedded matrix of mirrors: an unlikely device for capturing sunlight.
Name: Empty Mirrorcatch Box

Description: You have a rival at zee.
AvailableAt: She hunts far from London, picking off both other pirates and travellers who zailed too far.
LevelDescriptionText: 20|You have once again defeated the Pirate-Poet~30|You have dined with the Pirate-Poet~40|You have forged a rivalry with the Pirate-Poet~90|You have abandoned the Pirate-Poet to the zee~99|The Pirate-Poet has written her last verse~50|You have reached a rapport with the Pirate-Poet~10|You have defeated the Pirate-Poet~0|You have heard of the Pirate-Poet
Name: Encounters with the Pirate-Poet

Description: Something has gone TERRIBLY WRONG.
Name: ENGINE OVERLOAD

Description: Zee-beasts can overwhelm any ship ever built. The Eschatologue was designed to be the exception.
Name: Eschatologue-class Dreadnaught

Description: Various events have occurred, but there's probably no need to worry, probably.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Don't worry
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Everything is probably perfectly all right.
Name: Everything is Probably Perfectly All Right

Description: Increase this to 100 at the hidden workshop in Port Carnelian to convert your ship to a zubmarine.
LevelDescriptionText: 1| You can trade Zee-Ztories, Stygian Ivory, Outlandish Artefacts, or Extraordinary Implications to increase this.
Name: Experimental Modifications

Description: How can such a thing be? Who but you could understand what it means?
Name: Extraordinary Implication

Description: Thick plates of bone have developed over the orbits, as if to hide or protect them. They are smooth and cold to the touch. Irrigo light glimmers in the line of the jaw.
AvailableAt: These can be found in the Forgotten Quarter of London, which the Genial Magician can open for you.
Name: Eyeless Skull

Description: You've met the father of the Cladery Heir.
Name: Familiar with the Cladery Heir's Father

Description: You have a useful relationship with a coffee-house in Vienna.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You've established a useful relationship with a coffee-house in Vienna.~300|Your relationship with the Caf Ferstel has ended.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You've established a useful relationship with a coffee-house in Vienna.~2|You've sold coffee to your contact in Vienna.
Name: Favours: A Drop of Darkness

Description: A fierce old enemy of anarchists.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|An Understanding~2|A Particular Understanding
Name: Favours: A Gentleman of the Bureau

Description: You've made Khaganian friends.
Name: Favours: A Pewter Horsehead

Description: A shadowy figure has made you an offer.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You accepted the proposal~2|You agreed to smuggle souls from London to Mt Palmerston~3|You delivered souls to Mt Palmerston~4|You were paid~5|You've been asked to pick something up...~101|You refused the proposal~6|You were given a task...
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You accepted the proposal~2|You agreed to smuggle souls from London to Mt Palmerston~101|You refused the proposal~3|You delivered souls to Mt Palmerston~5|You've been asked to pick something up...~4|You were paid~6|You've been given a task...
Name: Favours: A Proposal from a Man of Business

Description: You've made friends among the beast-slayers of the Chelonate.
Name: Favours: A Whalebone Token

Description: You have done service for the Admiralty, and they won't forget it.
Name: Favours: Admiralty's Favour

Description: You have combed the zee for stories and other treasures.
Name: Favours: Antiquarian

Description: Your gifts to the Leopard Clan have assured you a little favour.
Name: Favours: Leopard's Condescension

Description: Your gifts to the Taimen Clan have assured you a little favour.
Name: Favours: Taimen's Mercy

Description: In the roof-tops of London, the Council conspires to end the rule of law.
Name: Favours: The Calendar Council

Description: A hundred dreams in every barrel.
Name: Firkin of Prisoner's Honey

Description: Flares may be used to reveal your enemies, increasing the speed of your firing solution.
Name: Flare

Description: We've all made mistakes. If only those mistakes could be left in the dark.
AvailableAt: Purchase these at Mrs Plenty's Shipside Provisioners.
Name: Foxfire Candles

Description: A scrap of lore. [Discover monsters and locations to gain Fragments. Gain enough Fragments, and they'll combine into a Secret.]
Name: Fragment

Description: Coal, dug from zee-cliffs or imported from Hell. [If you run out of fuel, you will drift helplessly.]
Name: Fuel

Description: Her eyes will hatch soon. But until then, she wants to work.
Name: Gall-Eyed Engineer

Description: Only the Chelonate could find this appetising.
Name: Gant Pole: A Barrel of Rancid Flesh

Description: You have been asked to deliver a message to Gaider's Mourn.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have been asked to deliver a message to Gaider's Mourn~2|You have delivered the message
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have been given a message.~2|You have delivered the message.
Name: Gant Pole: A Message From The Dead

Description: A picture emerges.
ChangeDescriptionText: 3|Blood still obscures the truth.~2|A pattern is emerging.~1|You can see nothing in the viscera.~4|You are on the edge of a revelation.
Name: Gant Pole: A Secret In Bones And Blood

Description: With the right spices, hungry people will eat anything.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Redolent Fleshmerchant has requested 'meath' from the Gant Pole~10|The Redolent Fleshmerchant is out of business
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Redolent Fleshmerchant has requested 'meath' from the Gant Pole.~10|The Redolent Fleshmerchant is out of business.
Name: Gant Pole: A Trade in Flesh

Description: The zee beyond Kingeater's Castle is dark and empty.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Sixth Witness asked you to visit the Gant Pole~2|You have the answer for the Sixth Witness at Kingeater's Castle~3|The Seventh Witness has looked East from Kingeater's Castle
Name: Gant Pole: A Witness to Nothing

Description: Secrets are buried in flesh and bone.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|It is all just a mass of entrails to you~4|You have learned how the Fading Haruspex performs her rituals~5|Patterns begin to emerge~3|Your stomach no longer jumps at the thought of divination~2|You have seen a spark of the truth
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are learning the ways of haruspicy.
Name: Gant Pole: An Apprenticeship in Haruspicy

Description: You are exploring this maze of twisted passages.
Name: Gant Pole: Corridors Of The Heart

Description: The knife is heavy in your hand.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are performing haruspicy.
Name: Gant Pole: Elbow Deep In The Nearly Dead

Description: This creature has little time left now.
ChangeDescriptionText: 7|The beast is strong. Its blood pumps thick and hard.~6|The beast's body thrashes in agony.~5|The beast's blood blackens. Viscous. Oily.~4|The beast's pulse weakens. It has little time left.~3|The beast moans. It barely has the energy to quiver.~0|The beast is silent. Its pain is over.~2|The beast shakes, mewling for the end.~1|The beast's final heartbeats pound their last.
Name: Gant Pole: Final Breaths

Description: Every step leads to your final destination.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The echo of silver writing glimmers in the darkness. "IT TORE OUT THE HEART. THE SHAME REMAINED."~2|A scowling pirate cleans his teeth with a dagger. The Gant Pole's depths are a fine place to hide, for those who can find it.~3|The tunnel twists into three directions. You lick your finger. The slight breeze guides your feet.~4|A gust of fetid air rushes through the tunnel. The heart shudders for a moment.~6|Slivers of calcified heart rain down from the cracked ventricle roof.~7|This ventricle narrows to a tight gap. Fossilised fat deposits crack under your feet.~8|The light of your candle flickers. In the darkness behind you, footsteps.~9|A group of Old Zailors sits in a circle, tearing strips off a recently arrived whale with their rotten teeth.~10|One of the Fading Haruspex's disciples scurries past, arms weighed down with supplies from deeper in the Gant Pole.~11|A gentle hum guides your feet forwards. Your eyes feel heavy. Somewhere here is a place you can sleep. You have earned your rest. There is no need to awaken.~12|You brush your hand against the rippled edges of the tunnel. Another ventricle. Was it flesh before it was stone?~13|You pass an encampment of zailors. They stare at you, refusing to talk. You move onwards and deeper into the Heart.~14|Water drips from a crack in the roof. You taste it. Stale and stagnant. Brine aftertaste. Still better than thirst.~15|In the distance, someone whistles a zee-shanty. It might be you.~16|The echo of silver writing glimmers in the darkness. "REJOICE, FOR THE END ALWAYS COMES."~17|You pass a wall covered in chalk-malks. Whether they mark days, years, or something else, whoever made them has been here for a very long time.~18|For a moment, you see a glow in the distance. It fades as soon as you look up.~20|Every tunnel twists and turns. Is a little treasure really so much to ask for in such a grim place?~5|Down this tunnel, you pass one of the Old Zailors writing something on the wall. In the light, it is invisible. In the darkness, illegible.~19|You pass a shack made of hide. The owner sleeps inside, gently breathing despite the polished bone of his skeleton visible through the decay and great chunks of devoured flesh. He cackles to himself about something in his dream, rolls over, and begins to snore.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You continue walking through the Gant Pole.~0|You have left the Gant Pole's ventricles.
Name: Gant Pole: Lost In The Darkness

Description: The Haruspex draws them from the viscera of the nearly dead.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|"There is a question waiting. It travelled in a ship long wreckd. Find it."~2|"The beast is tethered - but not forever. Refuge comes to London." ~3|"They were seven and they shall be seven again. Their names may change but the number remains." ~4|"The names of the heirs to Nidah will begin with M, A, R, I - which is rebellion." ~5|"Beneath the waves, two cities live. They grow. They hunger."~6|"Beware Anthe. It will change you. You will be sharp, keen as a knifes edge."~7|"The wound reopens; the flesh will not heal. Bring them your remorse." ~8|"They yearn for it: Liberty, Equality, Eternity."~9|"They are only mortal. They suffer too: Vitality, Infirmity, Fatality."~10|"The preacher travels to the bell tower. The bell, it- Oh god. That's horrid." ~11|"The one they fear waits in a pale cavern. The walls are carved with prophecies."~13|"The dream is great and ancient. It is fuelled by deeds of horror; none will have strength to deny it." ~14|"Wheels turn within wheels; a king yearns for your hand."~15|"One joins us below. The trespasser does not surface." ~16|"A question will not go unanswered indefinitely."~18|"The Salted will rise above the waves. They will find only their graves."~19|"An ancient beast wakes when the trespassers light pierces the abyss. The trespasser shall never know peace; only terror." ~20|"There shall be a new horizon. All shall know it - but the kings city will witness it first." ~12|"The Soldier fled, and smothered himself in freedom."~17|"Freedom is fragile. The beast will wake."
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The flesh reveals all.
Name: Gant Pole: Portents of the Deep

Description: A beast of the zee has gone to the Gant Pole.
LevelDescriptionText: 2|Triskelegant~3|Beloved~4|Behemoustache~1|Thalatte
ChangeDescriptionText: 0|The Gant Pole awaits its next weary beast.~1|A beast heads to the Gant Pole.
Name: Gant Pole: Something Ends

Description: She has her answer. It is time to return to Whither.
Name: Gant Pole: The Fading Haruspex

Description: Her time draws nearer.
LevelDescriptionText: 90|The Haruspex has returned home~99|The Haruspex has faded~1|The Haruspex clings to life a little longer~95|The Haruspex has returned home~3|The Haruspex is almost gone~4|The Haruspex prepares to breathe her last
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Haruspex fades a little more.~99|The Haruspex is no more.~90|The Haruspex has boarded your ship~95|The Haruspex has returned home~3|The Haruspex approaches her end.~4|The Haruspex prepares to breathe her last.
Name: Gant Pole: The Fading Haruspex

Description: Not all the elders of the zee swam.
Name: Gant Pole: The Secrets Old Zailors Keep

AvailableAt: Sometimes available for hire in London.
Name: Genial Magician

Description: A scholarly creature from a warlike nation of aristocratic guinea-pigs whose progenitors stole a steamer to escape the locked hutches of a London essayist.  Apparently.
Name: Guinea Page

Description: Equip and use it at zee to challenge the Pirate-Poet.
Name: Hand-Carved Ushabti

Description: A bucket of tiny but razor-toothed serpentlings.
Name: Harlot-Fry

Description: This is a marker quality that indicates you have a Harpoon weapon equipped.
Name: Harpoons

Description: Earnest, learned, prone to jump at loud noises.
AvailableAt: Sometimes available for hire in London.
Name: Haunted Doctor

Description: Inspire, heal, defend. [Sometimes helps with tests around Terror.]
Name: Hearts

Description: A message transmitted through the medium of death. [This is stored safely in your Lodgings.]
Name: Heirloom

Description: These do not grow on or under the world.
Name: Hesperidean Apple

Description: What is the festival for tonight?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Silent Reel~2|The Hour of Our Reflection~3|The Rainbowing
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You are participating in the Silent Reel!~2|You are participating in the Hour of Our Reflection!~3|You are participating in the Rainbowing!
Name: Hideaway: Celebrating a Festival

Description: Hideaway is at a turning point. Something will give way soon.
LevelDescriptionText: 100|The dwellers choose to believe that all's well~110|The dwellers refuse the truth~120|The dwellers are maintaining their belief that all's well~130|The dwellers don't want to acknowledge the truth~140|The dwellers are struggling to deny the truth~160|The dwellers cannot ignore the truth~150|The dwellers are beginning to accept the truth
Name: Hideaway: Deciding the Future of Hideaway

Description: A man with many questions is on your vessel.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|He has asked you to take him to Hideaway~2|He has asked you to take him to the Salt Lions
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|He has asked you to take him to Hideaway.~2|He has asked you to take him to the Salt Lions.
Name: Hideaway: The Impolite Investigator

Description: He has a mighty and terrible hope.
LevelDescriptionText: 40|You saved Arik's central control board	~50|You ensured that Hideaway will be well maintained for Arik~20|You helped Arik power an alternator~10|You helped the Sprightly Visionary set up an alternator
ChangeDescriptionText: 40|You saved Arik's central control board.~50|You ensured that Hideaway will be well maintained for Arik.~20|You helped Arik power an alternator.~10|You helped the Sprightly Visionary set up an alternator.
Name: Hideaway: The Sprightly Visionary's Ambition

Description: He has requested you unmask the Governor of Wisdom and demand he come to Hideaway.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Sprightly Visionary has made his request~2|Consigned to the zee~3|Accepted by the Governor
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Sprightly Visionary has made his request.~2|Consigned to the zee.~3|Delivered.
Name: Hideaway: The Sprightly Visionary's Request

Description: The dwellers of Hideaway are well aware of the truth of their situation. Aren't they?

ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You refused to answer the Impolite Investigator's question.~3|You gave the Impolite Investigator all he needed for an answer.~5|The Impolite Investigator was distressed by your answer.~10|There is a search for truth being conducted in Hideaway.~20|The Impolite Investigator has discovered a distressing truth about Hideaway.~50|The truth will be fought over during the Silent Reel.~40|It is a fact: Temtum will outgrow Hideaway, destroying the city. Name: Hideaway: The Truth

Description: Try to make the most of it.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The festival has begun!~5|The festival continues~10|The festival will soon conclude
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The festival has begun!~5|The festival continues.~10|The festival will soon conclude.
Name: Hideaway: Time Passing

Description: The dwellers of Hideaway don't trust those from outside.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|It will be more difficult to participate in the festivals of Hideaway for a while
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|It will be more difficult to participate in the festivals of Hideaway for a while.
Name: Hideaway: Wary of You

Description: How much space do you have?
Name: Hold

Description: You need to find somewhere better to live. And soon.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You should look for somewhere to live.~0|You've found somewhere to live!
Name: Homeless!

Description: What kind of shape is your ship in?
Name: Hull

Description: All of us must eat.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Replete~25|Fed~50|Peckish~100|Desperate~75|Ravenous
Name: Hunger

Description: Eat the flesh of the deep-lurkers, and your eyes will change.
Name: Hunter's Eye

Description: Your prey is vanquished, but this remains.
Name: Hunting-Trophy

Description: This desperate, demented device inflicts apocalyptic damage on even the greatest zee-beasts, but it fires only one thing: Monster-Hunters. [You may find them in the Chelonate and Khan's Shadow, and occasionally elsewhere.]
Name: Icarus in Black

Description: This choice is not yet available! It will be, some day.
AvailableAt: This choice is not yet available! It will be, some day.
Name: Impossible!

Description: Your rivals are a good way behind you.
Name: In the Lead

Description: Death, where is thy sting? Where indeed. Don't mess with the Campaigner, Death.
Name: Indomitable Campaigner

Description: The Gnomic Gallivant now knows his target's face.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Gnomic Gallivant now knows his target's face
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Gnomic Gallivant now knows his target's face.
Name: Information from the Cumaean Canal

Description: The Gnomic Gallivant discovered the whereabouts of his target.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Gnomic Gallivant discovered the whereabouts of his target
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Gnomic Gallivant discovered the whereabouts of his target.
Name: Information from the Iron and Misery Company

Description: Oh, I say! Someone will be interested.
Name: Intriguing Snippet

Description: The Pulp-Miners have been giving nerve-cord to the Hempen Man.
ChangeDescriptionText: 2| Pulp-miners have been trading Nerveline to the Hempen Man.
Name: Investigating Nook: A Bundle of Nerves

Description: Is this Hempen Man a Nooker? What is his connection to the Maw quakes?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Who is this Hempen Man? What is his connection to the Maw quakes? Is he even a Nooker?
Name: Investigating Nook: A Hempen Man

Description: The Hempen Man has build a drill. It bores slowly into the Maw.
Name: Investigating Nook: A Vile Drill

Description: Supplies and machinery are being diverted to the Cavities.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Supplies are being diverted down the gullet. Why?
Name: Investigating Nook: Missing Supplies

Description: Groups of disaffected youth are joining a cult which seeks the death of the Maw
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|The Hempen Man advocates killing the Maw. The Nerveless are his followers. Do the children follow him too?
Name: Investigating Nook: The Nerveless

Description: The missing Nook children once lived here.
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Mrs Collier clearly knows something about the missing children.~2|Mrs Collier allowed the Hempen Man to take her charges, in return for a promise to slay the Maw.
Name: Investigating Nook: The Orphanage

Description: Have you and the Cladery Heir been looking for something?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|Your future investigations with the Heir will be easier.
Name: Investigating with the Cladery Heir

Description: "I am the master of my fate: I am the captain of my soul." [You are in Unforgiving mode, with no save slots besides the basic autosave. You will lose this token if you switch from Unforgiving to Merciful mode.]
Name: Invictus Token

Description: DESTROY. Increases the damage your attacks do.
Name: Iron

Description: Cheery enthusiasm is a welcome, but unnerving, trait in a gunner.
AvailableAt: Sometimes available for hire in London.
Name: Irrepressible Cannoneer

Description: The King's Claw keeps order on the Isle of Cats.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|You have accepted Isery's Patronage~4|Delivered the Scholar's Notes to your Patron~2|Smuggling red honey to the Alarming Scholar~3|Delivered your shipment to the Alarming Scholar~5|Conducting Experiments in red honey~6|A successful experiment!~7|A friend of King's Claw~101|Refused Isery's friendship. Or lost it.
Name: Isle of Cats: Isery's Patronage

Description: She prefers Lady of the Gardens. Or just Zaira.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Accepted Zaira's Patronage~2|Smuggling red honey to the Merchant Venturer~3|Delivered the shipment to the Merchant Venturer~4|Passed the Venturer's Message to Zaira~6|Made a sacrifice to the Rose Garden~7|A friend of Zaira~101|Refused Zaira's friendship. Or lost it.
Name: Isle of Cats: Lady of the Cages' Patronage

Description: You are engaged in an activity too monstrous even to be truly illegal.
Name: Isle of Cats: Smuggling Red Honey

Description: A brooch of amber cat's eyes, and a warning.
LevelDescriptionText: 2|More "passing awareness" than notice, really~1|You are, almost entirely, beneath his notice~3|Your antics intrigue~5|You have his attention
Name: Isle of Cats: The Pirate-King's Notice

Description: Be sure their sins will find them out. [The Judgement Resonator does not limit your ability to hide.]
Name: Judgement Resonator

Description: Is this... a soul? It's pale and bright. Souls like this, they say, are the spores of strange gods.
Name: Judgements' Egg

Description: Its wings carry a thousand years of memories. Few of those memories are good.
Name: Keeper-Moth

Description: No-one has the Key of Dreams. This thing is coming soon.
Name: Key of Dreams

Description: This is a placeholder for a storyline associated with a character throughline.
AvailableAt: This is a placeholder for a storyline associated with a character throughline.
Name: Key of Faces

Description: This element is not yet implemented.
AvailableAt: This is not yet available.
Name: Key of Histories

Description: How will your kingdom be known?
LevelDescriptionText: 1|Aestival~2|New London~3|Lastport~4|Freedom~5|Utopia Beneath~6|Sophia~7|Fiddler's Gold~11|Sanctuary~12|The Empire of Trees~8|Peachtree Isle~10|Head Office~9|B____r Off
Name: Kingdom: a Name

Description: Tea is civilisation. But coffee is revolution. [Until this reaches 5, you can keep improving your Estate with coffee beans.]
Name: Kingdom: Coffee is Power

Description: Your estate grows.
Name: Kingdom: Estate

Description: Remember this day.
Name: Kingdom: Founded

Description: Intrigue might give you the leverage you need to survive as a nation. [Until this reaches 5, you can keep improving your Estate with Vital Intelligence.]
Name: Kingdom: Knowledge is Power

Description: Your subjects increase.
Name: Kingdom: Population

Description: Adorn your hall with glittering trophies.  [Until this reaches 5, you can keep improving your Estate with Artefacts.]
Name: Kingdom: Wealth is Power

Description: One rules in your absence.
LevelDescriptionText: 1|The Genial Magician~2|The Indomitable Campaigner~3|The Disillusioned Doctor
ChangeDescriptionText: 3|The Disillusioned Doctor is now your viceroy.~2|The Indomitable Campaigner is now your viceroy.~1|The Genial Magician is now your viceroy.
Name: Kingdom: your Viceroy

Description: You need nothing explained. On zubmarines, you are an expert.
Name: Knowledgeable About Zubmarines

Description: This is all of us, one day; but let's not be in a tearing hurry about it.
Name: Lamentable Relic

Description: Cramped and fragile, but remarkably nippy.
Name: Lampad-class Cutter

Description: Breathing faster doesn't help. That stinking headache won't shift. And could the ringing in your ears stop, just for a moment?
Name: Last Gasp

Description: "THE BOADICEA: MORE POWER, LESS SUBTLETY." The best Leadbeater & Stainrod can supply, although as usual they've skimped on materials.
Name: Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Boadicea'

Description: "Fear her touch!" One of L&S' more reliable pieces, which isn't saying much. Permits Flensing attacks.
Name: Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Britomart' Flensing-Cannon

Description: The 'Illyrian' is an outdated model, but it'll get you where you need to go.
Name: Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Illyrian'

Description: "THIS WAY UP." A weapon which may serve against small monsters or feeble pirates.
Name: Leadbeater & Stainrod Reconditioned Frigate-Surplus Deck-Gun Mark II

Description: A sting in your tail.
Name: Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Scorpion'

Description: 'Seaworm' torpedoes are small but lethal. Don't underestimate them.
Name: Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Seaworm'

Description: "WINNOW THE SLUMBERING GREEN!" Permits Torpedo attacks.
Name: Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Winnower'

Your chances will improve with every port you search: Whither, the Isle of Cats, Irem, the Chelonate, Khan's Shadow, Port Carnelian or the Surface port of Naples
Name: Learning About: Maybe's Daughter

Description: What draws him to the zee?

Description: What will she become?
LevelDescriptionText: 20|You answered the Exile's question.~5|You dined with the Exile.~10|You made a choice.~11|You've visited the Exile in her cabin.
ChangeDescriptionText: 5|You dined with the Exile.~10|You made a choice.~11|You've visited the Exile in her cabin.~20|You answered the Exile's question.
Name: Learning About: The Carnelian Exile

Description: You've grown closer. Is that safe?
LevelDescriptionText: 60|Seeking knowledge of the Cladery Heart in Adam's Way~70|Gaining knowledge of the Cladery Heart in Adam's Way~80|Learning how to retrieve the Cladery Heart~90|Seeking the Cladery Heart in Khan's Shadow~20|Aware of the Cladery Heir's claims of parentage~30|Informed of the Cladery Heir's (possible) relationship to Mr Iron~100|Still seeking the Cladery Heart in Khan's Shadow~110|Looking for the Cladery Heart in Frostfound~40|Gathering details on the history of the Cladery Heir~120|Determining the future of the Cladery Heart~121|Finished choosing the fate of the Cladery Heart~115|Retriever of the Cladery Heart, which awaits in Port Carnelian~10|Alerted to rumours about the Cladery Heir's parentage
